ci: refine triggers for `docker_publish` workflow
- Removed the trigger for the `docker_publish` workflow on push to `master` branch - Retained the trigger for the `docker_publish` workflow on the push of tags that match the pattern `v*` and on the schedule (7:00 AM every Sunday)
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: bump ffmpeg 7.0-1
- Upgrade the `ffmpeg` version from `6.1.1` to `7.0-1` in Dockerfile.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

build: optimize Dockerfile for smaller size and OpenShift compatibility
- Change Dockerfile comment to indicate final stage with requirements not installed for slower start but smaller size. - Add new Docker stage `final_requirements_not_installed` from `prepare_final`. - Add code to copy dependencies and Stable Diffusion web UI code with parameters to support arbitrary user ID for OpenShift best practice. - Introduce dumb-init as PID 1 to handle signals properly. - Set the application to listen on port 7860 with data directory /data, and to transform and allow code with new CMD entry.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: using upx to compress files in dist directory
- Separate the running of `launch.py` and `upx` into two different steps for testing in Dockerfile - Implement a new run command to find and compress certain files within the `/launch.dist` directory using `upx` - Add `--skip-torch-cuda-test` argument to the ENTRYPOINT declaration in the Dockerfile.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: refactor Dockerfile for enhanced testing and compression
- Separate the running of `launch.py` and `upx` into two different steps for testing in Dockerfile - Implement a new run command to find and compress certain files within the `/launch.dist` directory using `upx` - Add `--skip-torch-cuda-test` argument to the ENTRYPOINT declaration in the Dockerfile.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: Transition to Nuitka build target in docker compose
- Change the build target in the `docker-compose.yml` file from `final` to `final_nuitka`
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: refactor docker-compose configurations for data paths
- Un-comment and enable `--pin-shared-memory`, `--cuda-malloc`, and `--cuda-stream` flags in `docker-compose.forge.yml`. - Add `context` and `cache_from` fields under `build`, changing its structure from a single line comment to a multi-line comment with values in `docker-compose.yml`. - Change data locations: map AI data paths to D: drive and ensure Stable-diffusion model data resides under repository SSD. - Modify volume mappings to reflect these changes.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: add issing ARGs
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore(Nuitka): refactor Dockerfile for improved package handling
- Add nofollow imports for certain packages (torch, numba, xformers, triton, llvmlite) in the Dockerfile configuration - Copy additional site-packages (torch, numba, xformers, triton, llvmlite) from the build stage to `/app` in Dockerfile - Remove the `--skip-torch-cuda-test` flag from the ENTRYPOINT command - Change the copy order in the final stage of Dockerfile, adding `stable-diffusion-webui` to `/app` before copying local dependencies to `/home/$UID/.local`.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore(Nuitka): enhance Nuitka caching and enable specific plugins
- Define the environment variables to control where caches live including `CCACHE`, `DOWNLOADS`, `CLCACHE`, `BYTECODE`, and `DLL_DEPENDENCIES`. - Add additional dependencies in the Dockerfile including `ccache`, `clang`, `libfuse-dev`, and `upx` to the `apt-get install` command. - An additional cache mount has been added for Nuitka using the `--mount` and `id=nuitka-$TARGETARCH$TARGETVARIANT` options. - Changes to the `python3 -m nuitka` command include new flags and plugins like `--python-flag=nosite,-O`, `--clang`, `--lto=yes`, `--enable-plugins=implicit-imports`, `--enable-plugins=matplotlib`, `--enable-plugins=multiprocessing`, `--enable-plugins=pkg-resources`, and `--enable-plugins=upx`. - The `--disable-cache=all` flag has been removed from `python3 -m nuitka` command. - The `ENTRYPOINT` has been updated to include the `--skip-torch-cuda-test` flag for the `launch.bin` command, used to skip testing in the webui that is not compatible with Nuitka.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: add Nuitka compilation CI
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: expanded the list of included data files during Nuitka compilation
- Changed a comment within the Dockerfile to specify stage usage - Added additional comments to specify size and details of several Python packages during installation (`torch`, `xformers`, `facexlib`) - Expanded the list of included data files during `nuitka` invocation to include all `requirements*`, `.html`, `.js` and `.css` files - Added a link command that creates a symbolic link between `/usr/local/bin/python` and `/app/python3` in the final stage for `nuitka` - Excluded the action of copying dependencies from the `build_big` stage to the `final_nuitka` stage, effectively changing how dependencies and code are handled in the final stage for `nuitka` - Added a section to report stage for `nuitka` to copy `compilationreport.xml`
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: implement Nuitka compilation in Dockerfile
- Add a new stage to compile code with Nuitka in the Dockerfile - Add launch parameters and support for arbitrary uid for OpenShift best practice in final stage for Nuitka - Use dumb-init as PID 1 to handle signals properly and copy scripts from data/scripts to app/scripts in Dockerfile - Include additional commands for Nuitka compilation, including no-qt and transformers plugins, and the inclusion of several data directories and files - Add Nuitka report stage, copying the Compilation Report from the compile_nuitka stage - Add install build dependencies and Nuitka in compile_nuitka stage with cache management for better performance.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: refactor Docker workflows and enhance permission settings

- Redefined Docker stages as base, build, and final - Installed Pillow dependencies explicitly - Moved working directory to '/source' - Integrated Pillow and pillow-simd installation process - Removed libjpeg62 runtime dependency - Added UID and caching to docker-compose.yml build arguments - Included explicit cache mounts for multi-architecture support in build stage.
